    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "The fertilization and development of one or more offspring, known as an embryo or fetus, in a woman's uterus.,The condition between conception (fertilization of an egg by a sperm) and birth, during which the fertilized egg develops in the uterus. In humans, pregnancy lasts about 288 days.,The state or condition of having a developing embryo or fetus in the body (uterus), after union of an ovum and spermatozoon, during the period from conception to birth.,Pregnancy is the state or condition of having a developing embryo or fetus in the body (uterus), after union of an ovum and spermatozoon, during the period from conception to birth. (NCI)"
  } ],
  "http://desiree-project.eu/bckm#NCI_DEFINITION" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "The state or condition of having a developing embryo or fetus in the body (uterus), after union of an ovum and spermatozoon, during the period from conception to birth."
